"index_reference": "8479: self-examination, examples of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides numerous examples of self-examination, and its results. In particular, self-examination is often portrayed as leading to repentance.</p>\n<h2>Self-examination in the experience of Israel</h2>\n<h3>Self-examination at the entry into the promised land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1-Josh7:26\">JOS 7:1–7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:14\">JOS 24:14</a></p>\n<h3>Self-examination during the war with the Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:24-1Sam14:47\">1SA 14:24–14:47</a></p>\n<h3>Self-examination at the time of the exile</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:18-Jer31:20\">JER 31:18–31:20</a></p>\n<h3>Self-examination after returning from exile in Babylon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:9\">NEH 8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:5-Hag1:12\">HAG 1:5–1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:15-Hag2:19\">HAG 2:15–2:19</a></p>\n<h2>Self-examination by other nations</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:1–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Self-examination in the experience of individuals</h2>\n<h3>King David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3-Ps51:6\">PSA 51:3–51:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:1-2Sam12:13\">2SA 12:1–12:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:3-Ps32:5\">PSA 32:3–32:5</a></p>\n<h3>Job</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:1-Job42:6\">JOB 42:1–42:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The psalmists</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:59\">PSA 119:59</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:5\">PSA 42:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:11\">PSA 42:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:5\">PSA 43:5</a></p>\n<h3>The lost son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:17-Luke15:20\">LUK 15:17–15:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:22\">MAT 26:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:19\">MRK 14:19</a></p>\n<h3>Judas</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:25\">MAT 26:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:5\">MAT 27:3–27:5</a></p>",
